Let's see:
 - the renegotiations are supposed to be concluded in 7 rounds by March 2018 or so (before the Mexican presidential elections race heats up). The Mexican elections are on July 1, 2018;
 - the fourth round was just concluded, with little success. Big open issues remain. Agreement by March (or May) seems unlikely;
 - the US businesses are predominantly for keeping NAFTA and so is (so far) Congress;
 - if and when the renegotiated deal comes to Congress, they have only up or down vote (no amendments);
 - serving a notice of intent to withdrawal (as opposed to actual withdrawal) is within the powers of the President. Can he use it as (i) negotiating tactic; (ii) to stir his base, in the run-up to the 2018 elections?
